17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
18
19 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code ยง 16-22-501(a), concerning the intended
20 benefit that is required as an element of the unauthorized practice of law,
21 is amended to read as follows:
22 (a) A person commits an offense if, with intent to obtain a direct any
23 economic benefit for himself or herself, the person:
24 (1) Contracts with any person to represent that person with
25 regard to personal causes of action for property damages or personal injury;
26 (2) Advises any person as to the person's rights and the
27 advisability of making claims for personal injuries or property damages;
28 (3) Advises any person as to whether or not to accept an offered
29 sum of money in settlement of claims for personal injuries or property
30 damages;
31 (4) Enters into any contract with another person to represent
32 that person in personal injury or property damage matters on a contingent fee
33 basis with an attempted assignment of a portion of the person's cause of
34 action;
35 (5) Enters into any contract, except a contract of insurance,
36 with a third person which purports to grant the exclusive right to select and
